    "For instance, in refs.",
    "20,24, two-step preparation procedures are proposed, in which a magic state is injected onto an intermediate-sized code, where error detection is used to suppress errors, before injecting the intermediate-sized code onto a larger code.",
    "This method is compatible with the injection protocols we have presented here.",
    "We might also adopt the method presented in ref.",
    "25, in which the authors propose estimating the logical error on the injected state in the decoding step of state injection.It is worth remarking that these error-detection protocols can be improved by increasing the fraction of error events that can be detected."
